OL,3,CGuernsey States spent #44 million more
OL,4,Cthan it brought in during 2024
OL,6,FGuernsey's Chief Minister, Deputy
OL,7,FLyndon Trott, who is not standing in
OL,8,Fthis month's election, says: "The
OL,9,FStates cannot continue to rely on
OL,10,Freserves built up in the past to fund
OL,11,Fthe services of today and tomorrow.
OL,13,F"The new Assembly will need to
OL,14,Fimmediately focus its attention on the
OL,15,Fissue of improving public finances. I
OL,16,Fcannot stress enough how important
OL,17,Fthat is to the long-term prosperity of
OL,18,Fthe island."
